.TH "tpm_pcr_read" 9 "tpm_pcr_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_pcr_read \- read a PCR value from SHA1 bank
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm_pcr_read
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u32 pcr_idx "  ","
.BI "struct tpm_digest *digest "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
a \fIstruct tpm_chip\fP instance, NULL for the default chip
.IP "pcr_idx" 12
the PCR to be retrieved
.IP "digest" 12
the PCR bank and buffer current PCR value is written to
.SH "RETURN"
same as with \fBtpm_transmit_cmd\fP
